name: presquile-national-wildlife-refuge-narrative-report-for-the-period-september-1-to-decem-31-767cf
notes: This narrative report for Presquile National Wildlife Refuge outlines Refuge accomplishments from September through December of 1959. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions, habitat conditions, water conditions, and food and cover during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, big game animals, furbearers, predators, rodents, and raptors- is also covered. The Refuge development and maintenance section discusses physical developments, plantings, and wildfires. A progress report on field investigations and applied research is also provided. The public relations section of the report describes recreational uses, Refuge visitors, Refuge participation, and violations. Items of interest and N-R forms are attached.
